@nalind RFC.  Instead of expecting `EmptyLayer` layers to exist, expect them not to exist, and modify c/image/storage to ignore them when pulling images.

This is pretty much the opposite to the attempt in #762 (which expected `EmptyLayer` to exist, as they do in v2s1, but they don’t exist at all in v2s2/OCI).

See also https://github.com/projectatomic/buildah/pull/775#issuecomment-396321518 , the
```go
		if img.TopLayer != lastLayer {
			logrus.Debugf("error creating image: image with ID %q exists, but uses different layers", intendedID)
			return errors.Wrapf(storage.ErrDuplicateID, "image with ID %q already exists, but uses a different top layer", intendedID)
		}
```
check could be broken.  We could just remove it, or maybe compute both the top non-empty and top possibly-empty layer, and allow reusing images with either.
